    <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Hold table-level metadata: unique identifier (for cross-referencing), page number, rotation angle, and optional title. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b I/O\/ \:  (page_id, uid, rotated_angle, title) -&gt; JSON serializable model</para>
<para>Holds the information about table unique identifier, rotation angle (if table has been rotated - for images) and so on.</para>
<para>:ivar page_id: number of the page where table starts :ivar uid: unique identifier of the table (used for linking table to text) :ivar rotated_angle: value of the rotation angle by which the table was rotated during recognition :ivar title: table&apos;s title</para>
<para>:vartype page_id: Optional[int] :vartype uid: str :vartype rotated_angle: float :vartype title: str </para>
    </detaileddescription>
